Antarctica has experienced its highest temperature on record at 17 . 
 5°C last week . 
  The temperature was recorded on the northern tip of the Antarctic Peninsula . 
  Over a two day period temperatures reached 17 . 
 4°C (63 . 
 3°F) This is potentially a new record for the warmest temperature measured on the frozen continent . 
  The heatwave was measured by sensors at Argentina's Esperanza Base . 
  The new temperature record was measured last week but has not been officially certified by the World Meteorological Organisation . 
  Antarctica is the coldest place on Earth but is also one of the fastest warming places on Earth . 
 